<subSubSection pageId="639" pageNumber="640" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xestonotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="639" pageNumber="640" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Xestonotus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853c: 383. Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Selenophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="639" pageNumber="640" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="639" pageNumber="640">Selenophorus lugubris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1829 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="639" pageNumber="640">xestos</emphasis>
(smoothed, polished) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="639" pageNumber="640">notos</emphasis>
(back, by extension dorsum) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="639" pageNumber="640" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">One North American species in the temperate regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="639" pageNumber="640" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">
The species is included in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lindroth’s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1968: 864) monograph.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="639" pageNumber="640" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="639" pageNumber="640">
Lindroth (1968: 864) regarded this taxon as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="639" pageNumber="640" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="639" pageNumber="640">Anisodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while Noonan (1973: 347) treated it as a valid genus. As discussed by Bousquet and Tchang (1992: 760), larval characters support 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Noonan’s">Noonan's</normalizedToken>
view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
